--------[ 2025-04-20 19:30:00 ] #During experiment gains, no longer in use
# We found a bug in the way we calculated the new HV settings previously (18th - 20th) due to a mistake in comparing the list of TET values in order of channel index, to a list of HV settings by HV crate, slot, and channel. This led to some channels being set to 1550V which should not have been, and some channels being set too low when they should have been set to 1550V. These updated gains and HV's should accomplish the following. We used the new gain factors from Provakar's elastic calibration to find new TET values assuming we want to see signals above 5mV(20fadc) at an energy of 40MeV. Any calculated TET value below 20fadc was set to 20fadc. The gain factors corresponding to the channels with a TET below 20fadc were changed to 0.01GeV/pC or 0.2MeV/fadc. The gain factors were also limited to go no lower than a gain corresponding to -1550V HV setting for that channel. The new gain factors were put into the ecal fadc config file and the online databse for ecal.We recalculated HV settings with the correct comparison of lists. Once again, these HV's are limited to not go above 1550V, so we also recalculated updated gain factors based on the channels which we set to 1550. These gain factors are updated in the ecal fadc config file as well as the online DB for ecal.

